TheArmy of the Czech Republic(lang-csArmáda České republiky) comprise the land forces, theCzech Air Forceand support units. From the late 1940s to 1989, the extensiveCzechoslovak Armed Forces(about 200,000) formed one of the pillars of theWarsaw Pactmilitary alliance. After the dissolution of Czechoslovakia, theCzech Republicis completing a major reorganisation and reduction of the armed forces, which intensified after the Czech Republic joinedNATOon 12 March 1999.Balance in Europe 2011"., March 07, 2011.
